	<p key="PowerFantasyVR">Power Fantasy VR</p>
	<p key="PowerFantasyVR/content">
		<figure>
			<img src="/slothsoft@daniel-schulz.slothsoft.net/static/images/PowerFantasyVR.jetpack" alt="Power Fantasy VR" />
		</figure>
		<article>
			<h2>About</h2>
			<p>
				Power Fantasy VR was created for a seminar of the Master's study of
				<a href="https://computerspielwissenschaften.uni-bayreuth.de/" rel="external" target="_blank">Computerspielwissenschaften
				</a>
				at the University of Bayreuth.
			</p>
		</article>
		<article>
			<h2>Technical Details</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					Made with
					<a data-dict-replace="spec/unity" />
					.
				</li>
				<li>
					It uses the
					<a data-dict-replace="spec/manus" />
					gloves and the
					<a data-dict-replace="spec/vive" />
					headset and trackers for a fully immersive virtual reality experience.
				</li>
				<li>
					Hand gesture recognition is implemented using machine learning algorithms provided by
					<a data-dict-replace="spec/ml.net" />
					.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</article>
		<article>
			<h2>Credits</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Katharina Broswik (programming, game design, modelling)</li>
				<li>Magnus Drebenstedt (level design, sound design)</li>
				<li>Daniel Schulz (programming, game design)</li>
			</ul>
		</article>
		<article>
			<h2>Links</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<a href="https://github.com/Faulo/PowerFantasyVR" rel="external">
						<q>Power Fantasy VR</q>
						on GitHub
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="/Downloads/PowerFantasyVR.zip" rel="external">Download (Win64)</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</article>
